						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the ruined temple of Śiva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 986</hi> and other details are not known, in which case the date of the record may be 1064 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Mutilated. It registers a grant of twelve <hi rend="italic">vīsās</hi> made by Brammi Reḍḍi and others, the lords of • • • • • divōḍu to the god Nishṭhanāthadēva for the merit of their parents, during the regime of Bramme-Nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
